The police officer, who lost his life in Kebbi State when the bandits attacked the convoy of the state’s Deputy Governor, Colonel Samaila Yonbe (retd.), has been identified as Assistant Superintendent of Police, Idris Libata. The Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Nafiu Abubakar, in an interview with our correspondent, said contrary to an earlier report, he was not killed in the attack. Libata was among the security personnel, who escorted the deputy governor to Kanya village on a condolence visit to the families of vigilante members, who were murdered by bandits. In a WhatsApp message sent to our correspondent, Abubakar stated, “I am the PPRO Kebbi State Police Command and I am alive.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com